overview: The user needed to add database functionality and an admin dashboard
  to a sleep questionnaire application. The agent evaluated the existing
  codebase, identified missing components, and proposed a plan. Key decisions
  included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for the database, implementing
  a simple password-based authentication system, and building an admin dashboard
  to view and export questionnaire responses. The authentication system was
  initially designed with custom session management but was later streamlined to
  leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient route protection. The agent
  provided comprehensive instructions for database setup and successfully
  verified the core functionalities through browser testing.
